data.title: Generational Group advises JMPE Electrical Engineering's sale to Agathos AEC, a Hunter Forest Capital portfolio company.
data.description: A mergers and acquisitions advisory firm, Generational Group, recently facilitated the sale of JMPE Electrical Engineering to Agathos AEC, a company under Hunter Forest Capital, for an undisclosed amount. The deal was finalized on February 2, 2026. JMPE Electrical Engineering, headquartered in Santa Barbara, California, is known for its comprehensive electrical engineering and lighting design services catering to various clients in the commercial, industrial, government, and residential sectors.

data.title: MATIC unveils Open Money Stack merging $2.3T infrastructure with Coinme buy, streamlining stablecoin payments. #Polygon #MATIC
data.description: Polygon Labs recently released details on the technical structure of Open Money Stack. This innovative system merges a massive $2.3 trillion settlement infrastructure with the acquisition of Coinme. The integration aims to establish comprehensive stablecoin rails, offering end-to-end solutions for users.

data.title: If UBS' bearish view on US stocks materializes, traders may shift to Bitcoin due to overvaluation concerns.
data.description: A recent UBS report highlighted that US stocks are considered to be "overvalued," indicating that there may be more favorable investment prospects in markets outside of the US. This observation has raised speculation on whether this could potentially serve as a driving factor for the next surge in Bitcoin value.

data.title: AV, Inc. to announce 3rd quarter fiscal year 2026 earnings on March 10, 2026, after market close. Conference call at 4:30 pm ET.
data.description: Arlington-based company AeroVironment, Inc. (NASDAQ: AVAV) is set to release its financial results for the third quarter of fiscal year 2026, which concluded on January 31, 2026. The market anticipates this report after the closing bell on March 10, 2026. Following the release, a conference call and live audio webcast are scheduled at 4:30 p.m. Eastern Time on the same day to delve into the figures. The call will be headed by Wahid Nawabi, AV’s chairman, president, and CEO, alongside Kevin P. McDonnell, the firm's executive vice president and chief.

data.title: Teledyne Marine and M Subs collaborate for UK Royal Navy opportunities, signing MOU for strategic partnership.
data.description: In NORTH FALMOUTH, Massachusetts, Teledyne Marine and M Subs have signed a Memorandum of Understanding (MOU) to collaborate on maritime unmanned underwater vehicles and marine technologies. Teledyne Marine, a renowned global leader in the industry, joins forces with M Subs, a UK-based innovator in marine unmanned systems and autonomy. The partnership's goal is to capitalize on each organization's strengths to pursue business opportunities linked to the UK Royal Navy. This strategic collaboration signifies a new chapter in the industry, combining Teledyne Marine's expertise with M Subs' innovation to drive growth and advancements in maritime technologies.
